records.addlTxt: The person shall be held for appearance in court.BODY ONLY

8:22 AM Defendant Juan Carlos Martinez Rodriguez not in court. DA Nolen appeared in person. Atty Jair Alvarez appears via zoom. The DE has been deported. DA Nolen requests a bench warrant, body only, continental US and a bail bond forfeiture hearing in 30 days. The Court grants the bench warrant.
Bail/Bond Forfeiture Hearing scheduled for November 16, 2022 at 09:00 am.
Bail/Bond Forfeiture Hearing on November 16, 2022 at 09:00 am.

12:08 PM Defendant Juan Carlos Martinez Rodriguez not in court.  Attorney Craig Nolen in court for State of Wisconsin.  Attorney Jair Chamuel Alvarez in court for Juan Carlos Martinez Rodriguez. Matter set over.
Status conference scheduled for August 19, 2022 at 08:30 am.
Status conference on August 19, 2022 at 08:30 am.

1:20 PM Defendant Juan Carlos Martinez Rodriguez in court, in custody.  Attorney Craig Nolen in court for State of Wisconsin.  Attorney Jair Chamuel Alvarez in court for Juan Carlos Martinez Rodriguez. Maria Marin sworn on oath as interpreter. Preliminary hearing waiver form filed with the Court. Defendant freely and voluntarily waives his right to a preliminary hearing. The Court accepts the waiver. Court finds probable cause.  Defendant bound over for trial. Information filed.  Court advises defendant of charges & penalties. Paper copies have been provided to the defense. Defendant waives reading of information. Not Guilty plea entered on all counts. Attorney Alvarez filed a motion to modify bond. Attorney Nolen believes bond was appropriate set on July 5, 2022. Parties argue bond. No bond modification done at this time. Defense may request a review hearing. Matter set over.
Pre-trial conference scheduled for August 2, 2022 at 08:30 am.
